
⸻

BudBuddy Project – 15.09.2025

⸻

Backend (Node.js + MongoDB)

Initial Setup
	•	Created backend.js with Express server.
	•	Added dotenv for environment variables.
	•	Installed and configured mongoose for MongoDB integration.
	•	Connected backend to local MongoDB (mongosh) and tested connection.

User Authentication
	•	Created User.js Mongoose schema with email and password.
	•	Added /register route:
	•	Password hashing with bcrypt.
	•	Validation: unique email.
	•	Added /login route:
	•	Password verification with bcrypt.compare.
	•	JWT token generation for secure authentication.
	•	Fixed issues where Swift could not decode _id or username:
	•	Adjusted JSON response to always include _id, username, and email.
	•	Removed duplicate /login routes.
	•	Updated User.js schema to include username field.
	•	Added instructions and commands to reset MongoDB users (db.users.deleteMany({})).

Error Handling
	•	Added proper error responses for:
	•	Invalid credentials.
	•	User not found.
	•	Duplicate registrations.
	•	Logged backend errors for easier debugging.

⸻

Frontend (SwiftUI)

AuthViewModel
	•	Centralized AuthViewModel to manage:
	•	Current logged-in user (currentUser).
	•	JWT token (token).
	•	Async login and register methods.
	•	Removed old loggedIn state variables.
	•	SwiftUI views now observe authVM.currentUser for navigation changes.

LoginView
	•	Implemented Apple-style input fields:
	•	Rounded corners, subtle icons in HStack, visible in light and dark mode.
	•	Semi-transparent backgrounds (Color.white.opacity(0.25)).
	•	Added input validation:
	•	Email format check.
	•	Password minimum 6 characters.
	•	Displayed inline error messages:
	•	Field-specific (under inputs).
	•	General login error if backend fails.
	•	Styled login button consistently with HomeView.
	•	Wrapped in ReactiveBackgroundView and FloatingMoodBackground (sativa/indica).
	•	Fixed navigation: no longer creates ContentView() inside LoginView; relies on authVM.currentUser in ContentView.

RegisterView
	•	Similar styling as LoginView with matching backgrounds and Apple-style inputs.
	•	Added username field with validation (min 3 characters).
	•	Error messages for email, password, username.
	•	Handles backend registration errors.
	•	Buttons styled to match LoginView.

ContentView
	•	Conditionally shows:
	•	TabView with Home, Activities, Strains, Extras when authVM.currentUser exists.
	•	LoginView when no user is logged in.
	•	Passed authVM to all child views.
	•	Reacts dynamically to authVM.currentUser updates, replacing login screen immediately after login.

HomeView
	•	Added profile button at top-right:
	•	Displays initials or placeholder icon.
	•	Navigates to ProfileView.
	•	Added logout button in ProfileView:
	•	Clears authVM.currentUser and authVM.token.
	•	Layout fixes:
	•	Safe area padding and spacers to avoid overlapping content.
	•	Styled background consistent with other views.

ProfileView
	•	Shows actual user data from authVM.currentUser:
	•	Username
	•	Email
	•	Profile initials fallback
	•	Logout button added below user info.

Styling / Visuals
	•	Reactive backgrounds updated:
	•	Light mode now has slightly darker bottom gradient to highlight FloatingMoodBackground.
	•	.indica, .sativa, .hybrid gradients adjusted to match dark mode style.
	•	Input fields made more visible in light mode.
	•	Buttons and text standardized across LoginView, RegisterView, and HomeView.

Additional Features
	•	Created UserProfileProtocol:
	•	Supports adding user description and other properties.
	•	Error handling improvements:
	•	Inline validation messages in login/register.
	•	Backend error messages displayed clearly.

Debugging & Utilities
	•	Added console logs in SwiftUI to inspect login/register data.
	•	Added curl/Postman examples for backend testing.
	•	Commands to reset MongoDB user collection for clean testing.

⸻

Summary
	•	Backend: Fully working auth system with JWT, password hashing, MongoDB integration, and proper error handling.
	•	Frontend: Fully functional SwiftUI login/register flow with unified AuthViewModel, live updates, profile and logout functionality.
	•	Styling: Consistent Apple-style inputs, reactive backgrounds, dark/light mode consistency, profile button.
	•	Validation: Inline field and backend error messages added for user feedback.
	•	User Experience: Immediate TabView access after login, proper navigation, profile and logout integrated.

